> Everyone's a winner when these customizable chicken quesadillas hit the table.
> Start with three fillings that are perfect for mixing and matching—fajita-spiced
> dark meat chicken, hearty black beans, and melty shredded cheese. Then, everyone
> can finish their quesadillas with sour cream, guacamole, and hot sauce on top,
> just the way they like it!

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add
@diced skinless dark meat chicken{10%ounce} in a single layer; season with half
the @fajita spice blend{1%tablespoon}, a pinch of @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Cook,
stirring occasionally, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired. Turn off heat; transfer chicken
to a #plate{}. Wash out pan.

While chicken cooks, drain and rinse @black beans{1%unit}.

In a #medium microwave-safe bowl{}, combine beans, @chicken stock concentrate{1},
remaining fajita spice blend, @water{2%TBSP}, @butter{1%TBSP}, @salt{1/2%tsp},
and pepper (for 4 servings: 4 TBSP water, 2 TBSP butter, and 1 tsp salt). Cover
tightly with #plastic wrap{} and microwave until beans are warmed through,
~{2-3%minutes}.

Mash about half the beans with a #potato masher{} or #fork{}. Taste and season
with salt and pepper if desired.

> If you added any other items to your meal (apps, sides, and/or dessert), you
> can get started on them now!

Arrange @flour tortillas{6}, chicken, beans, and @Mexican cheese blend{1%cup} family
style for everyone to assemble their own quesadillas.

> Place filling of your choice on one half of a tortilla; fold tortilla in half
> over filling to form a quesadilla.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in pan used for chicken over medium heat. Add
quesadillas and cook on one side until golden brown, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Carefully flip quesadillas; cook until golden brown and cheese melts,
~{1-2%minutes} more.

> Work in batches if needed, adding another drizzle of oil between batches and
> reducing heat if quesadillas start to brown too quickly.

Halve quesadillas.

Serve quesadillas with @sour cream{3%tablespoon}, @guacamole{4%tablespoon}, and
@hot sauce{1%teaspoon} on the side.

> Don't forget to serve with any extra items you may have ordered to build out your
> meal!

> Poultry is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.